name: Addictingly Spicy Cheeseburger Dip
author: FuzzyEyes
summary: An addicting cheese dip that is a must for parties. The Colby cheese makes it thick enough to dip with no mess. Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.
ingredients: 1 (16 ounce) jar mild picante sauce (such as Pace®)
1 (16 ounce) jar hot picante sauce (such as Pace®), or less to taste
⅓ pound shredded Colby cheese, or more to taste
1 (1 pound) package processed cheese food (such as Velveeta®), cut into cubes
directions: Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat
Cook and stir beef in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes; drain and discard grease
Pour mild picante sauce and hot picante sauce over the ground beef; stir
Add processed cheese food and Colby cheese, reduce heat to low, and cook until the cheese is completely melted, about 15 minutes
